thoughts on charles simic the new u s poet laureate favorite poem reflections on his work i'm thrilled you asked i've been spending a lot of time with him lately er i mean his writing he actually got me back into writing before these last few days i hadn't written for about a year anyway onto your question i've been carrying the world doesn't end around with me for the last few weeks one of my favorites dear friedrich the world's still false cruel and beautiful earlier tonight i watched a chinese laundry man who doesn't read or write our language turn the pages of a book left behind by a customer in a hurry that made me happy i wanted it to be a dreambook or a volume of foolishly sentimental versus but i didn't look closely it's almost midnight now and his light is still on he has a daughter who brings him dinner who wears short skirts and walks with long strides she's late very late so he stops ironing and watches the street if not for the two of us there'd be only spiders hanging their webs between the streetlights and the dark trees this poem makes me happy to be Time Out of Mind Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Knots Landing Neil Gaiman The Catcher in the Rye The Ashlee Simpson Show C. S. Lewis Charles Simic Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Louis MacNeice Spidey Super Stories Japanese poetry Marilyn Monroe The Subtle Knife Novel Characters in the Smurfs Theory of conduct Waka The Amber Spyglass K' StarCraft: Uprising American Psycho AFI 100 Years series Sharon Tate Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Samuel Taylor Coleridge The Jam Humphrey Bogart The Lovely Bones Objectivist poets The Contender (television series) Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Night (book) William Shakespeare Salad Fingers William Wordsworth EastEnders The Tale of Genji Negima James Russell Lowell Blood on the Tracks Social rule Skirt and dress Hiberno-English The Raven TLC 24 Hours of Le Mans Adam Mickiewicz Gary Snyder Pakistani cricket team in West Indies in 2005 Publication of Darwin's theory John Cage Slayers Robert Browning Rent (musical) Charles Dickens The Apprentice 2 E. E. Cummings Charles Bukowski Beauty and the Beast (1991 film) Major League Baseball television contracts Doris Day Samuel Beckett Miss Saigon Conan the Barbarian Louis Zukofsky Futurama (TV series - season 5) Emperor Yuan of Han The Family from One End Street Suit (clothes) Imagism Phil Collins Frankie Laine Literature Performance poetry English poetry Jeopardy! in culture Rudyard Kipling Daredevil Stephen King Venom (comics) Anglo-Saxon literature Haven (TNG episode) All My Children Kodocha Alice Liddell Treehouse of Horror V James Hanratty Philosophy of language Gundam W G-Unit: Last Outpost Ernest Hemingway Infidels Kitchen Johann Gottfried Herder Ancient Greek literature 